# RunModel

This directory contains the main implementation of the numerical simulation model.

The code in this folder is responsible for initializing the physical parameters, solving the governing differential equations using the Runge-Kutta numerical method, and managing the complete simulation workflow. It represents the core computational engine of the project.

Major responsibilities include:

- Initialization of simulation parameters
- Numerical integration of governing equations
- Time evolution of physical variables
- Data generation for post-processing
- Preparation of outputs for visualization

Most modifications to the simulation algorithm should be performed within this directory.
